    <text>
        <body>
            
            <div1 type="letter">
                
                <pb facs="nei.j4c.12.8" />
                <note type="curatorial">House Collection</note>
                <fw type="letterhead">
                Editorial Department        ST, LOUIS POST-DISPATCH
                <lb/>
                ST. LOUIS, MO.</fw>
<opener>                
<dateline>Feb. 27 '27</dateline>

<salute>Dearest Comrade:</salute>
</opener>
<p>Don't worry about this moment in a silly but necessary social experiment. Of course the rabble isn't educable.</p>

<p>We are doing something - you and I - that will outlast this twilight.</p>

<p>Signs of the growing success of the scheme are increasing.</p>

<p>I'm glad you're in the world with me.</p>
<closer>
<salute>Endless love,</salute>

<signed>Jno.</signed>
</closer>
</div1>
            
            <div1 type="envelope">
                <ab type="postmark">St. Louis Mo. Feb 27 12-PM 1927
                REGISTER OR INSURE VALUABLE MAIL</ab>
                <figure>
